unnel-type dynamics, as\nobserved in protein folding, is a consequence of evolution subjected to thermal\nnoise beyond a certain level; this also leads to mutational robustness of the\nfitness.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Jun 2009 12:40:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Jun 2009 05:31:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 8 Sep 2009 06:01:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
