{"id":"0906.0939","submitter":"Bao-An Li","authors":"Gao-Chan Yong, Bao-An Li, Lie-Wen Chen and Xun-Chao Zhang","title":"Triton-$^3$He relative and differential flows as probes of the nuclear\n  symmetry energy at supra-saturation densities","comments":"Discussions added. Version accepted by PRC","journal-ref":"Phys.Rev.C80:044608,2009","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevC.80.044608","report-no":null,"categories":"nucl-th nucl-ex","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Using a transport model coupled with a phase-space coalescence after-burner\nwe study the triton-$^3$He ratio, relative and differential transverse flows in\nsemi-central $^{132}Sn+^{124}Sn$ reactions at a beam energy of 400 MeV/A. The\nneutron-proton ratio, relative and differential flows are also discussed as a\nreference. We find that similar to the neutron-proton pairs the triton-$^3$He\npairs also carry interesting information about the density dependence of the\nnuclear symmetry energy. Moreover, the nuclear symmetry energy affects more\nstrongly the t-$^3$He relative and differential flows than the $\\pi^-/\\pi^+$\nratio in the same reaction. The t-$^3$He relative flow can be used as a\nparticularly powerful probe of the high-density behavior of the nuclear\nsymmetry energy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Jun 2009 15:50:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 29 Sep 2009 19:42:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-29"}
